Students protest over NSFAS allowance. #eNCA speaks to NSFAS spokesperson, Slumezi Skosana. JOHANNESBURG - The Wits SRC is expected to meet with officials from the Department of Higher Education and the National Student Financial Aid Scheme in another bid to resolve matters. This comes after they met with Gauteng Premier Panayza Lesufi. READ: Wits University talks deadlock There is still no concrete resolution to the conflict between Wits management and students. The protest action continued on Monday with students vowing to up the ante. Striking Nehawu workers at the university joined the student protest on Monday. Students have been protesting over financial exclusion, student accommodation, and higher residence allowances. #eNCA's Silindelo Masikane follows the story. #DStv403